caption.text:
Share this video with someone who loves traveling! We are just two days away from our SECOND TO LAST COUNTRY on our trip to visit every country in the world!!

There have been lots of ups and downs on our journey the past 8 years to visit all 50 states and now almost every country. So it's hard to believe we are this close to accomplishing a dream we weren't sure could ever happen!

Sooo grateful for all the people we've met along the way who have been such a blessing to us, and for all of you following along with our trip!

P.S. Since we're asked every video, the two countries that are left are the Bahamas (this week!) and Sudan (waiting on for next year due to the war and humanitarian crisis there).
__________________________

Want to travel more? We got you! We're an American travel couple on a mission to visit every country. We have traveled full-time for 8 years. Follow for the best destinations to visit and tips to help you travel more!

#travel #travelcouple #everycountry #adventuretravel #couplestravel #travelcouples #traveltips

caption.text:
Easy Summer Travel Inspiration!!🌊🎬
.
Hope you enjoy this fun travel B-Roll I made quickly while visiting a restaurant!!☺️ Glad to be back and sharing with you all it’s been a little while - got lots of stuff planned ahead so looking forward to sharing it with you all!😎
.
Comment your thoughts below and if you’d like a tutorial!😊🙌
.
#filmmaker #filmmaking #behindthescenes #transition #filmmakers #mobilephotography #summer

caption.text:
Here’s how you can do this too👇🏼

Follow @tayandtreytravel first! We’ll teach you how to travel like this too for CHEAP!

✔️ Budget intentionally: Cut back on eating out and unnecessary spending. 

✔️Travel smart: Book during shoulder seasons, stay just outside major tourist areas, and use public transport when possible. 
 
✔️ Use what you’ve got! Do you have a car? A tent? An IPhone to film? A cooler to pack food? 

✔️ Pick up side gigs: We did family photos, senior sessions, and small branding shoots to build our travel fund. 

✔️ Get into UGC (user-generated content):Yes, hotels and brands will pay you and offer free stays in exchange for content — you don’t need a huge following! 

✔️ If you want to be a content creator, just start posting consistently. It’s easier to grow than you think, and brands care more about quality and trust than follower count.

user.full_name: Tay & Trey Poulter | Adventure Travel Couple

caption.text:
dual income, no kids, just vibes and visa stamps. redefining how life should look like as 29 & 30 yr old couple. ✈️

We met 7 years ago and from the very first date, we connected the most over sharing our travel stories from different parts of the country. By the end of the date, there was a common question looming large - when will we get a chance to travel together?

From the beginning of our relationship, we prioritised travel, even if that meant taking off to a nearby destination only for the weekend. 

By the time we were all set to get married, we were pretty notorious for the couple that travels out of a wedlock. It is hardly a surprise how many people advised us subtly to now “settle down after marriage.” Basically, follow the path that they have known all their lives - get married, buy a house, become parents, and what not!

I say, if our careers are not traditional, why should our lives be?

We just want to chase a few wild dreams first.

What about you?

Share this with someone you’d love to make this dream come true. 

#travelgoal #coupletravel #relationships

caption.text:
Stay for FREE as a Couchsurfer 💵❌

It’s been one of my most used apps in my backpacking days! It’s a paid annual subscription, but it’s still such a travel must-have if you ask me, not just to stay but also to meet other travelers/locals in the city/town you’re visiting!

Here’s what you need to know-
🎒You can sign up as a Host and/or a Surfer
🎒 The stay can be as listed by the host, and you can choose what suits you best- from literally a couch in their living room, to a mattress on the floor, a shared room or a private room..you can pick what works and is available
🎒 Yes, you really do NOT need to pay a single penny, there are no transactions to book.
BUT, it’s unspoken Couchsurfer code to carry a gift for your host, spend some time with them, and generally be respectful of their space and generosity
🎒 Much like any other booking app, you can filter to find a host with references (aka reviews), a verified host, gender, etc
🎒 As you build your reviews/references as a Surfer, it makes hosts that much more likely to accept your invitation

And that’s it!
Would you try this?

#couchsurfing #travelbudget #travelonabudget #budgetravel #backpacking #travelreels

We are just two days away from our SECOND TO LAST COUNTRY on our trip to visit every country in the world!!

There have been lots of ups and downs on our journey the past 8 years to visit all 50 states and now almost every country. So it's hard to believe we are this close to accomplishing a dream we weren't sure could ever happen!

Sooo grateful for all the people we've met along the way who have been such a blessing to us, and for all of you following along with our trip!

P.S. Since we're asked every video, the two countries that are left are the Bahamas (this week!) and Sudan (waiting on for next year due to the war and humanitarian crisis there).
__________________________

Want to travel more? We got you! We're an American travel couple on a mission to visit every country. We have traveled full-time for 8 years. Follow for the best destinations to visit and tips to help you travel more!

income, no kids, just vibes and visa stamps. redefining how life should look like as 29 & 30 yr old couple. ✈️

We met 7 years ago and from the very first date, we connected the most over sharing our travel stories from different parts of the country. By the end of the date, there was a common question looming large - when will we get a chance to travel together?

From the beginning of our relationship, we prioritised travel, even if that meant taking off to a nearby destination only for the weekend. 

By the time we were all set to get married, we were pretty notorious for the couple that travels out of a wedlock. It is hardly a surprise how many people advised us subtly to now “settle down after marriage.” Basically, follow the path that they have known all their lives - get married, buy a house, become parents, and what not!

I say, if our careers are not traditional, why should our lives be?

We just want to chase a few wild dreams first.

What about you?

Share this with someone you’d love to make this dream come true.

for FREE as a Couchsurfer 💵❌

It’s been one of my most used apps in my backpacking days! It’s a paid annual subscription, but it’s still such a travel must-have if you ask me, not just to stay but also to meet other travelers/locals in the city/town you’re visiting!

Here’s what you need to know-
🎒You can sign up as a Host and/or a Surfer
🎒 The stay can be as listed by the host, and you can choose what suits you best- from literally a couch in their living room, to a mattress on the floor, a shared room or a private room..you can pick what works and is available
🎒 Yes, you really do NOT need to pay a single penny, there are no transactions to book.
BUT, it’s unspoken Couchsurfer code to carry a gift for your host, spend some time with them, and generally be respectful of their space and generosity
🎒 Much like any other booking app, you can filter to find a host with references (aka reviews), a verified host, gender, etc
🎒 As you build your reviews/references as a Surfer, it makes hosts that much more likely to accept your invitation

And that’s it!
